Description: Provides an R interface to the FastKernelSurvivalSVM model 
    from the Python 'scikit-survival' package. The package enables fitting 
    Survival Support Vector Machines for right-censored outcomes using 
    kernel methods. Users may employ native kernels from 'scikit-learn' 
    or define custom kernel functions directly in R. Computation is 
    delegated to the Python implementation via 'reticulate', while a 
    clean R API is provided for fitting, predicting, evaluating and 
    summarizing survival SVM models, including optional parallel bagging 
    using 'mirai' and 'purrr'.
URL: https://github.com/prdm0/FastSurvivalSVM
BugReports: https://github.com/prdm0/FastSurvivalSVM/issues
